Scaling is the method that is used for increasing or decreasing the number of virtual machine instances based on demand. There are two main ways to scale:
Manual Scaling –> You can set the exact number of VM instances you want. You do scaling manually.
Automatic Scaling –> The system adjusts the number of VM instances automatically based on rules and metrics, such as CPU utilization, memory usage, or incoming traffic.
For example, if CPU usage exceeds a set threshold for a defined duration, the scale set can automatically add more VM instances for load balancing. 
Conversely if usage drops, it can remove instances to save resources and cost.
